# OPERSERV
Op: /operserv mode <channel> +o <nickname>
Deop: /operserv mode <channel> -o <nickname>
Admin: /operserv mode <channel> +a <nickname>
De-admin: /operserv mode <channel> -a <nickname>
Voice: /operserv mode <channel> +v <nickname>
Devoice: /operserv mode <channel> -v <nickname>

Kick: /operserv kick <channel> <nickname> <reason>
Ban: /operserv mode <channel> +b <hostmask>


# SA
Force part: /sapart <nick> <channel> <reason>
Force join: /sajoin <nick> <channel>
Force nickchange: /sanick <nick> <new nick>
Kick: /sakick <nick> <channel> <reason>


# GET INFORMATION ABOUT USER
Look after someone with same hostmask: /check <nick/hostmask>

Information about user: /whois <nick>
More information about user: /whois info <nick>

IP of user: /userip <nick>

NickServ information about user: /nickserv info <nick>

What irc-client: /ctcp <nick> version
What time user got: /ctcp <nick> time
How long ping use: /ctcp <nick> ping


# OP/DEOP
/mode <channel> +o <nick>
/mode <channel> -o <nick>


# SEND OUT MESSAGE
Send out a message on all chats I'm on: /ame <message>
Send out message to everyone everywhere: /global 


# OPER LOGIN/OUTLOG
Log in as ircop: /oper <username> <password>
Log out as ircop: /mode <nickname> -o


# JOIN CHANNEL OVERRIDE
Join channel with override: /join <channel> override


# OFTEN USED COMMANDS WHICH DOES NOT REQUIRE CHANSERV RIGHTS
Kick: /kick <channel> <nick> <reason>
KILL: /kill <nickname> <reason>
GLINE: /gline <hostmask> <duration>: <reason>
Ban with time: /tban <channel> <duration> <hostmask>
Prevent nick changes: /mode #<channel> +b N:<hostmask>


# DIVERSE
/chanserv set <channel> mlock off
